yoruba_text: Ará bìnrin kan tá a máa pe orúkọ rẹ̀ ní Kíkẹ́, ṣà làyé pé “inú òtítọ́ ni wọ́n bí òun sí, tí wọ́n sì ti tọ́ òun dà gbà,” à mọ́ nígbà tó wà lọ́mọ ọdún mẹ́rìndínlógún, ó fi ìjọ Ọlọ́run sílẹ̀ lá ti lọ máa lépa “à wọn ohun tó ń fani mọ́ra nínú ayé.”
english_text: One sister, whom we will call Tanya, explains that she was “raised around the truth,” but when she was 16, she left the congregation to “pursue worldly enticements.”

yoruba_text: (Kólósè 1:9, 10) Ọ̀nà pà tàkì méjì ni a lè gbà tọ́jú ìrísí wa nípa tẹ̀mí.
english_text: (Colossians 1:9, 10) We cantake careof our spiritual appearance in two main ways.

yoruba_text: Bó tilẹ̀ jẹ́ pé ohun tó ṣe é yìí le gan-an, tí à wọn dókí tà kan sì sọ pé tí wọ́n ò bá fẹ́ kó kú, ó yẹ kí wọ́n fa ẹ̀jẹ̀ sí i lá ra, à wọn tó ń tọ́jú rẹ̀ sọ pé ohun tó kọ sínú ìwé yẹn là wọn máa tẹ̀ lé.
english_text: Although his condition was serious and some doctors felt that to save his life, blood transfusion was necessary, the medical staff waspreparedto honor his wishes.

yoruba_text: (10) Kí ni à wọn oníṣègùn tí iye wọn túbọ̀ ń pọ̀ sí i ti ń múra tán lá ti ṣe bá yìí fún à wọn Ẹlẹ́rìí Jèhófà, kí ló sì ṣeé ṣe kó wá di ìlà nà ìtọ́jú tí wọ́n á máa lò fún gbogbo alá ìsàn bí à kókò ti ń lọ?
english_text: (10) What are a growing number of physicians willing to do for Jehovah's Witnesses, and what may eventually become the standard of care for all patients?
